messages.message:
@Bastiane glad to hear! note that this is a preview release from them and i don't think the implementation is perfect. i'm sure it struggles with many things that GPT does off the shelf - tables/layout, lengthy docs, in context memory etc. it's effectively a bolt on with a clever validation technique.

that said, i agree we should be considering reusability - a robust prompt library, slick UI & preview windows (w/pricing), easily exposed APIs - all the things i know we're actively thinking about!
